
    1. Access to https://github.com/AirenSoft/OvenPlayer
    2. Download it by pressing the Clone or Download button and clicking Download ZIP in the menu that appears.
    3. Unzip the OvenPlayer-0.9.zip
    4. Move to OvenPlayer-0.9 -> dist -> production
    5. Copy a ovenplayer folder
    6. Paste to your webServer static folder
    7. Import to ovenplayer path on your html
    Like this <script src="your_static_path/ovenplayer/ovenplayer.js"></script>
    8. Following the Quick Start menu https://github.com/AirenSoft/OvenPlayer
   

If you donâ€™t have a web server. But you need a web server.
Please consider the following methods:

   1. Install a Nginx for CentOS7. (https://www.nginx.com/resources/wiki/start/topics/tutorials/install/)
    sudo yum install epel-release
    sudo yum install nginx
   2. Move to Nginx root directory
    cd /usr/share/nginx/html
   3. Download OvenPlayer
    git clone https://github.com/AirenSoft/OvenPlayer.git
   4. Access to browser
    http://YOUR_IP/OvenPlayer/docs/demo.html

If the above process is difficult, use the public server we have prepared.

http://demo.ovenplayer.com
